710734f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 56th Street
710734f-a.text:
Eleventh Ave. (right, foreground), cast side, south from
West 57th(left, foreground) to 56th Streets, showing the foundation
of the New Sheffield Farms plant under construction. The New York
Central Railroad tracks shown will be enclosed and two private
sidings built for the sole service of this company. The buildings
shown to the left and at the rear of this clearance will shortly be
demolished and their sites added to permit this ultra modern milk
plant to extend to its full length of 550 feet. The photographer is
viewing in a southeastward direction to show silhouetted against the
sky the 42nd 5treet and Times Square building outline.
1937..
Gift of New York Central System
Publicity Bureau.

710735f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 56th Street
710735f-a.text:
Eleventh Ave. (right, fore to background), east side, south from
West 57th (center, right to left) Street, showing the new Sheffield
Farms plant under construction on the westerly portion of the 57th to
56th Street block. Beneath same runs the new road bed of the New York
Central Railroad which appears on the right emerging at a tangent to
cross the Avenue to the 60th Street yards. The old plant to the rear
of this new building will be razed and the new structure extended
shortly. Two private railroad sidings service this enterprise.
July 24, 1937.
0ift of New York Central System
Publioity Bureau.
